---  
description: Use when writing TypeScript props for Sitecore React components and deciding between default JSS fields, GraphQL data.datasource fields, or context-only page fields.  
globs: ["src/components/**/*.ts", "src/components/**/*.tsx", ".sitecore/component-map.ts"]  
alwaysApply: false  
---  
  
Match the React props shape to the rendering configuration.  
  
1. Rendering HAS `ComponentQuery`  
- Use GraphQL shape  
- Access parent datasource at `fields.data.datasource`  
- Access child items at `fields.data.datasource.children.results`  
- Field names are camelCase  
- Editable fields use `.jsonValue`  
  
2. Rendering has NO `ComponentQuery`  
- Use default JSS shape  
- Access fields directly on `fields`  
- Field names are PascalCase  
- Values use `.value`  
  
3. Context-only rendering  
- No datasource fields  
- Read from `page.layout.sitecore.route.fields`  
- Use `page.layout.sitecore.context.itemPath` for breadcrumbs  
  
Never mix these shapes in one component.  
  
Quick examples:  
- GraphQL: `fields?.data?.datasource?.title?.jsonValue`  
- Default JSS: `fields?.Title`  
- Context-only: `page?.layout?.sitecore?.route?.fields?.Title`  
  
Always use optional chaining for nested access.  